  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6813.61 trading above the 6804 GEX flip in a PIN regime, dealers are currently long gamma and will sell into strength while buying weakness, creating stabilizing flows. The massive positive gamma wall at 6830 (+77B) represents a key resistance level where dealer selling pressure intensifies, while the market sits comfortably within the high-gamma zone between 6810-6830 that should promote mean reversion. Watch for potential breakout attempts above 6830 to shift the dynamic, but current positioning favors range-bound action with dealers providing liquidity against directional moves.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect the market to grind sideways between 6810-6830 with limited breakout potential.",
